<dl id="n29219e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n29" href="#n29219e">N29 (VI.B.21)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n29all.htm#n29219e"> 219(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hearty cheerful &amp; easy</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In 1866 Mr. Dodgson was introduced to Miss Charlotte M. Yonge, whose novels had long delighted him. &ldquo;It was a pleasure I had long hoped for,&rdquo; he says, &ldquo;and I was very much pleased with her <mark>cheerful and easy</mark> manners&rdquo; <small> Stuart Dodgson Collingwood, <a name="SDCL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SDCL"><cite title="source">The Life and Letters of Lewis Carroll</cite></a> ([1912]) 94</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: H.C. &amp; E. </mm> </dd></dl>
